orders: Sergei Obraztsov and Soviet Travels to London in the 1950s / rGilburd, Eleonory -- t12. Adventures in the Marketplace: Yugoslav Travel Writing and Tourism in the 1950s-1960s / rBracewell, Wendy -- t13. East German Nature Tourism, 1945-1961: In Search of a Common Destination / rMoranda, Scott -- t14. Coping with the Tourist: Planned and "Wild" Mass Tourism on the Soviet Black Sea Coast / rNoack, Christian -- tList of Contributors -- tIndex  aIn the Soviet Union and the eastern bloc, the idea of "vacation" was never as uncomplicated as throwing some suitcases in the car and heading for the beach. The emphasis was on individual self-improvement within the framework of the collective, an approach manifest in everything from the scheduling of physical exercise to the group tours organized for factory workers, Party cadres, and other segments of society. Like other Soviet-style utopian projects, socialist tourism, which was often heavily laden with rules and prescriptions, was a consciousness-raising project, part of the vast effort to forge new socialist men and women.Turizm is the first book to examine the history of tourism in Russia and eastern Europe from the tsarist period to the age of Soviet and east European mass tourism in the 1960s and 1970s. The contributors to this volume address topics including the roots of socialist tourism, the role of tourism in the making of nations and maintenance of empire, and ways in which the men and women of the "margins of Europe" understood themselves in relation to "Europe." Especially interesting are chapters that show how individuals pursued their own consumerist goals within the framework of collective tourism, obliging the regimes to adapt. Illustrated with period photographs and promotional materials, Turizm will appeal not only to historians of the region but also to anyone with an interest in consumer culture, travel, leisure, and nation-building.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 16. Mai 2019) 0aTourismzEurope, EasternxHistoryy19th century. 0aTourismzEurope, EasternxHistoryy20th century. 0aTourismzRussiaxHistoryy19th century. 0aTourismzSoviet UnionxHistory. 0aTouristszEurope, EasternxHistoryy19th century. 0aTouristszEurope, EasternxHistoryy20th century. 0aTouristszRussiaxHistoryy19th century. 0aTouristszSoviet UnionxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Russia & the Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh1 aGorsuch, Anne E., eeditor.1 aKoenker, Diane P., eeditor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCOR eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066750940uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/9781501727238423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501727238.jpg  a978-3-11-066750-9  COR eBook-Package 2000-2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG